Little Crater Lake Trail

easy
(234)
Mount Hood National Forest
  • Photos (379)
  • Directions
  • Print/PDF Map
  • Share
  • More

Explore this 0.3-mile out-and-back trail near Government Camp, Oregon. Generally considered an easy route, it takes an average of 5 min to complete. This is a popular trail for birding, camping, and hiking, but you can still enjoy some solitude during quieter times of day. The best times to visit this trail are May through October. Dogs are welcome, but must be on a leash.

Length0.3 miElevation gain0 ftRoute typeOut & back
Dogs on leashWheelchair friendlyKid friendlyStroller friendlyCampingHikingWalkingBird watchingLakeRiverWildflowersWildlife
â¢ SEASONAL ROAD CLOSURE: Roads within and around Mount Hood National Forest are subject to seasonal closure and/or chain requirements. For more information, please visit https://www.fs.usda.gov/detail/mthood/alerts-notices/?cid=stelprdb5191108 This is a cute walk through a gorgeous meadow, into the forest, and out to an amazing little lake. The water is bright blue, and you can see all the way down. Swimming of any kind is not allowed in Little Crater Lake. Additionally, dogs are not allowed in the lake. Accessibility: This trail is likely accessible for visitors using wheelchairs, mobility equipment, or strollers. According to the park website, this trail is barrier-free trail. Accessible Parking: Number of designated accessible spaces: unclear; Parking lot surface: paved. Trail Details: Trail surface: packed gravel; Average trail width: 4 feet; Estimated average grade category: flat (1% or less).
Travel Oregon, 670 Hawthorne St, Suite 240 , Salem, OR, 97301, Phone: 800-547-7842
Directions from Rhododendron: Travel south on Highway 26 approximately nine miles past its junction with Highway 35. Turn south on Forest Service Rd. 42 for approximately 3.5 miles, then turn right (west) onto Rd. 58. Follow 58 for 2 1/4 miles to the entrance of Little Crater Campground. The trailhead is located in the campground.
